description: A hammer is a hand tool,fixed to a long handle that is swung to deliver an impact to a small area .
A measuring tape used for measuring length. It is made up of materials like fiberglass, cloth, plastic, metal ribbon, or strip.
A screwdriver is an essential tool used to install and remove — as well as tighten or loosen—screws.
A drill is a tool used for making round holes or driving fasteners. It is fitted with a bit, either a drill or driverchuck.
Step ladders bring you a few feet off of the ground, allowing you to perform home improvement tasks.
A chainsaw is a portable gasoline or electric saw that cuts with a set of teeth attached to a rotating chain driven along a guide bar.
